 invoke class static init. However, line 529 will only initialize if `sun.misc` is present, which isn't the case on JDK21. Maybe I should add a version-agnostic test for `getSizeMethod`, but I’m unsure about skipping tests. The reflection in JDK21 complicates things, especially if `JavaLangAccess` is absent and leads to null results. This could be tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering line 529 coverage**\\n\\nI see there’s no coverage for line 529, but if `sun.misc` is present, we could achieve it. Should I go ahead and add that? It might involve hardcoding `sun.misc`, but that's simply how the source behaves. If I test natively without `sun.misc`, it returns null, meaning the test would pass. I need to weigh the implications of this decision and how hardcoding might affect things down the line.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking Gradle dependencies**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the Gradle implementation dependency might be using an old version of Guava, possibly with some sun.misc classes included in the Gradle jar. But I think Class.forName(..., null) might not be the right approach. I don’t want to overcomplicate things, so perhaps the best move is to check the git diff and clarify this. It’s always good to double-check and make sure everything is as it should be!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_L4xenFvaMrqqk4wEWP5Agrun|fc_07967c35b4b391cf016a4268d665cc81948ae3ea6f0dd6b7ce", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && git diff -- tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-gradle-resolver/3.33.1/src/test/java/io_quarkus/quarkus_bootstrap_gradle_resolver/OrgGradleInternalImpldepComGoogleCommonBaseThrowablesTest.java", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 27391, "output": 875, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45162, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse"