text", "text": "No additional safe coverage change is possible for the remaining call site under the current rules.\n\nThe remaining site:\n\n- `Throwables.getSizeMethod(Throwables.java:529)`\n- `getStackTraceDepth.invoke(jla, new Throwable())`\n\nis only reachable when Guava/Gradle’s shaded `Throwables` can load legacy bootstrap JDK classes:\n\n- `sun.misc.SharedSecrets`\n- `sun.misc.JavaLangAccess`\n\nOn the current JDK, those legacy APIs are not present in the bootstrap class loader, so `getJlaMethod(...)` returns `null` and `getSizeMethod(...)` exits before line `529`.\n\nReaching the site would require patching or injecting fake `sun.misc` classes into `jdk.unsupported`/bootstrap, but that would violate the instruction:\n\n> Do not create source stubs, fake replacements, or shadow classes for library or dependency API types in their real packages.\n\nSo I left the remaining call site unreached rather than adding forbidden stubs or Native Image-hostile dynamic class injection. The previous test already covers the other active-class dynamic-access site.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07967c35b4b391cf016a426959b78881948b7fe29f86cb40c0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1270, "output": 1973, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49323, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782737213329, "responseId": "resp_07967c35b4b391cf016a42693dea5c81949c35d30ce821c2f6"}}
