ses for dependency/JDK API types in their real packages.\n\nSo I did not add another test or broaden the patch. The active class currently has the reachable dynamic-access site covered, and this remaining site should stay unreached with the above explanation.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07967c35b4b391cf016a4269a8022481949bb7d0aae027973c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6243, "output": 1236, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48439, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782737302342, "responseId": "resp_07967c35b4b391cf016a42699783bc81949687a12c41eacdfd"}}
